{"title": "Poem for a Survivor",
  "author": "Donald Justice",
  "text": ["Holding this poem",
    "Close, like a mirror,",
    "I breathe upon it.",
    "I watch for some sign.",
    "There is a faint mist",
    "Spreading across it.",
    "",
    "It takes hold. It clings",
    "To the lean hollows",
    "As the sun rises,",
    "",
    "This sun that is going",
    "To burn the mist off.",
    "",
    "I give you chamois",
    "To clear the surface.",
    "",
    "I give you this sun."]
}